A vintage-style illustration of an aged, magnificent oak tree in autumn, where one half is lush with golden leaves and thriving branches reaching toward the sky, while the other half shows bare, brittle limbs being carefully pruned by an ornate pair of brass gardening shears floating in mid-air. The pruned side reveals hollow, decaying wood inside. At the base of the tree, small saplings aggressively sprout from the ground, their vibrant green shoots already climbing toward the weakened branches. The scene is rendered in warm sepia tones with hand-drawn crosshatching textures, reminiscent of 1920s botanical illustrations and vintage business periodicals, with a slightly weathered paper texture overlay.
